verbose_text: Thus, the structural characteristics of MtrF support the notion that bacterial surface localized c-Cyts MtrC, MtrF, and OmcA transfer electrons directly to the surface of Fe (III) oxides via their solvent exposed hemes, such as heme 5 or 10 of MtrF.
